  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. The <em>y</em>-intercept of a graph in the <em>xy</em>-plane is the point where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. For the given equation, the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph in the <em>xy</em>-plane can be found by substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> in the equation, which yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals minus one fourth left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis squared plus 2 left parenthesis 0 right parenthesis plus 29\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mn>0</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>29</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 29\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>29</mn></math>. Therefore, the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma 29 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>29</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. It&rsquo;s given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi></math> is the estimated number of scheduled deliveries <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> months after the end of May <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2012\"><mn>2012</mn></math>. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> represents <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0\"><mn>0</mn></math> months after the end of May <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2012\"><mn>2012</mn></math>, or the end of May <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2012\"><mn>2012</mn></math>. Thus, the best interpretation of the <em>y</em>-intercept of the graph of this equation in the <em>xy</em>-plane is that at the end of May <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2012\"><mn>2012</mn></math>, the estimated number of scheduled deliveries was <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"29\"><mn>29</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual errors.</p>",
